				"name": "appcd-default-plugins",
				"description": "Pseudo package for all default appcd plugins"
			}
		],
		"description": "Now that there are multiple major versions of appcd plugins, we need figure out a way to ship them. Some tools depend on v1, others on v2. We need both.\r\n\r\nIdeally plugins would be installed via the AMPLIFY Package Manager, but we're not quite there yet. So, it makes sense to use {{appcd-default-plugins}} as the package.\r\n\r\nThe appcd plugin system does support a nested plugin directory scheme, but this is incompatible with {{node_modules}}. So we'll likely need a pre-publish task that organizes the files appropriately and efficiently.",
